args: Nice one, Nino! You're a natural!
You think so? I've never seen anything\nlike this thing of yours that uses mana\nto slide along the snow.
It's called a snowboard. Pretty slick\ninvention, if I do say so myself.
It's amazing you could whip something\nlike this up out of materials we found\nat the kidnappers' hideout.
And now that I've made it once, I can\ncrank these babies out by the ton!
Well, we've got the presents in order.\nAll that's left is to make our deliveries!

When we had to go to a big town to get
the presents, I was worried we might not
make it—but I think we're gonna pull it off
thanks to these snowboards!
I couldn't do it without you helping me\nout, so seriously, thank—BLARGH!
I'm fine, but why the heck did it just\nbreak like that? I don't... Oh!
I'm glad you're unharmed,\nbut your snowboard...
Not likely. I saw a bunch of parts go flying\nwhen I wiped out, and finding them here\nwould be a pretty big ask.
(And I highly doubt there's anything we\ncan substitute for those parts just\nhanging around nearby...)
(Maybe I should just have Nino deliver\nthe presents without me?)
(No, that won't work. We'll only finish in\ntime if we're both on snowboards.)
(Think, lady! Think! There's gotta be\nsomething to get us outta this mess!)
Ilia, you should use my board.
I appreciate the sentiment, but we can't\ndeliver all of these with just one of us.
I know. That's why I want you to use it.
Whoa! Hang on, are you sure?
You looked pretty shaken when it came up\nearlier, so I figured you didn't want anyone\nto see it.
I'd be lying if I said I wasn't afraid of\npeople seeing it...
But I can't ignore a friend in need,\nand I won't use that as an excuse to do so.
With my wing out, I can match your speed\non your snowboard. Now let's quit talking\nand just do this already!
Right. Let's get this show on the road!
He came to my house too! He really WAS\nwatching over us this whole time!
Look! Saint Starfall came for me as well!
Saint Starfall's real! He's really real!
Hey, you're that nice man from yesterday!
Did Saint Starfall come to your house\ntoo, mister?
He certainly did—and he left this\nby my pillow!
Ooo! What a pretty little bird!
Hey, we should all show off our presents!
Well, the kids certainly seem fond of him.\nThat's the one you were buying a present\nfor, right?
Sure is—and I was pretty worried about\nwhat to get him too.
But turns out he's just thrilled to get a\npresent in the first place. It's a real weight\noff my shoulders, lemme tell you.
And mine as well. Thanks to this, I feel\nconfident I can give my present too.
Did you finally manage to find something\nfor that picky Paladyn of yours?
I did indeed. He told me he likes to read,\nso I got him an embroidered bookmark.
Oh, that's a GREAT gift! Those reader-types\ncan never have enough bookmarks.
Are you not going to ask about my wing?\nDon't you think it's odd that a human\nwould have one?
Hey, it's not like a wing or three is gonna\nchange how we feel about each other.
And I'd never force a friend to talk about\nsomething they're uncomfortable with.
You haven't asked about my name either!
It gets complicated having the same name\nas the Goddess, so I try to keep it on the\ndown-low as much as I can.
Heh. This is just like when we first met.
Back then, we were both worried about\nwhat presents to get, and now we're\ntrying to hold on to our secrets!
And while there are so many things I'd like\nto talk to you about...I should go.
Got a final present to deliver, eh?
After all the effort I went to picking it out,\nit would be a shame not to deliver it.
Can we see each other again, Ilia?
The Goddess will make sure of it.
Well then, have a merry Dragonyule.
I know we'll see each other again.\nAfter all, she brought us together.
(That beautiful wing was just like yours.\nIt really brought me back...)
Oh, she's already gone on her way.
Aw. I wanted to show her my present.
Did Saint Starfall visit you, Ilia?
He sure did—and he came with the best\npresent in the world.
(To think she'd send me a friend a\nthousand years in the future... Heh.\nThat really is just like Meene.)
